# Testing Guidelines

This file contains test guidelines for Cursor IDE

## Guidelines

1. Follow the Better Specs guidelines always that it is possible
2. Prefer BDD/Gherkin approach for writing style
3. Prefer tests using tables as arguments to dry-up the code
4. Use Busted for automating Lua code testing
5. Use [shellspec](mdc:https:/shellspec.info) for automating shell script testing 
6. Use [shellspec](mdc:https:/shellspec.info) for automating Makefiles target testing
7. Use Testcontainers (<https://testcontainers.com>) is used for automating container testing
8. Keep tests minimal and focused
9.  Document any special requirements
10. Include test cases where possible